4.12	Marry_You	Marry You	"Marry You" is a song by American recording artist Bruno Mars, released as the fourth single internationally from his debut studio album, Doo-Wops &amp; Hooligans. Mars wrote the song with his production team The Smeezingtons, who also produced the track. "Marry You" incorporates influences of reggae and R&amp;B. Lyrically, the song sees Mars singing about a spontaneous marriage idea. It received generally mixed reviews from most of the critics, with some complimenting its production and Mars' vocals on the song.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e3/Bruno_Mars_Marry_You_cover.jpg/220px-Bruno_Mars_Marry_You_cover.jpg
